Suspected herdsmen have invaded a Catholic seminary in Jalingo, Taraba state on Monday morning.

Daily Trust gathered that they injured some priests and students.

Evaristus Bassey, director of Caritas Nigeria, an agency of the Catholic Church, confirmed this to TheCable- an online Newspaper on Monday morning.

A priest was reportedly shot during the attack while two others were beaten up.

